Document: MultiMesh
Path: godot/classes/class_multimesh.rst
Summary: This section describes the properties available for configuring a MultiMesh resource, including instance data, mesh, and rendering options.

Property Descriptions:
*   **buffer** (PackedFloat32Array): No description available. Default: PackedFloat32Array().
    Method: set_buffer(value: PackedFloat32Array)
    Method: get_buffer() → PackedFloat32Array
    Note: The returned array is copied and any changes to it will not update the original property value. See PackedFloat32Array for more details.
*   **color_array** (PackedColorArray): Array containing each Color used by all instances of this mesh.
    Deprecated: Accessing this property is very slow. Use set_instance_color() and get_instance_color() instead.
    Note: The returned array is copied and any changes to it will not update the original property value. See PackedColorArray for more details.
*   **custom_aabb** (AABB): Custom AABB for this MultiMesh resource. Setting this manually prevents costly runtime AABB recalculations. Default: AABB(0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0).
    Method: set_custom_aabb(value: AABB)
    Method: get_custom_aabb() → AABB
*   **custom_data_array** (PackedColorArray): Array containing each custom data value used by all instances of this mesh, as a PackedColorArray.
    Deprecated: Accessing this property is very slow. Use set_instance_custom_data() and get_instance_custom_data() instead.
    Note: The returned array is copied and any changes to it will not update the original property value. See PackedColorArray for more details.
*   **instance_count** (int): Number of instances that will get drawn. This clears and (re)sizes the buffers. Setting data format or flags afterwards will have no effect. By default, all instances are drawn but you can limit this with visible_instance_count. Default: 0.
    Method: set_instance_count(value: int)
    Method: get_instance_count() → int
*   **mesh** (Mesh): Mesh resource to be instanced. The looks of the individual instances can be modified using set_instance_color() and set_instance_custom_data().
    Method: set_mesh(value: Mesh)
    Method: get_mesh() → Mesh
*   **physics_interpolation_quality** (PhysicsInterpolationQuality): Choose whether to use an interpolation method that favors speed or quality. When using low physics tick rates (typically below 20) or high rates of object rotation, you may get better results from the high quality setting. Default: 0.
    Method: set_physics_interpolation_quality(value: PhysicsInterpolationQuality)
    Method: get_physics_interpolation_quality() → PhysicsInterpolationQuality
    Note: Fast quality does not equate to low quality. Except in the special cases mentioned above, the quality should be comparable to high quality.
*   **transform_2d_array** (PackedVector2Array): Array containing each Transform2D value used by all instances of this mesh, as a PackedVector2Array. Each transform is divided into 3 Vector2 values corresponding to the transforms' x, y, and origin.
    Deprecated: Accessing this property is very slow. Use set_instance_transform_2d() and get_instance_transform_2d() instead.
    Note: The returned array is copied and any changes to it will not update the original property value. See PackedVector2Array for more details.
*   **transform_array** (PackedVector3Array): Array containing each Transform3D value used by all instances of this mesh, as a PackedVector3Array. Each transform is divided into 4 Vector3 values corresponding to the transforms' x, y, z, and origin.
    Deprecated: Accessing this property is very slow. Use set_instance_transform() and get_instance_transform() instead.
    Note: The returned array is copied and any changes to it will not update the original property value. See PackedVector3Array for more details.
*   **transform_format** (TransformFormat): Format of transform used to transform mesh, either 2D or 3D. Default: 0.
    Method: set_transform_format(value: TransformFormat)
    Method: get_transform_format() → TransformFormat
*   **use_colors** (bool): If true, the MultiMesh will use color data (see set_instance_color()). Can only be set when instance_count is 0 or less. This means that you need to call this method before setting the instance count, or temporarily reset it to 0. Default: false.
    Method: set_use_colors(value: bool)
    Method: is_using_colors() → bool
*   **use_custom_data** (bool): If true, the MultiMesh will use custom data (see set_instance_custom_data()). Can only be set when instance_count is 0 or less. This means that you need to call this method before setting the instance count, or temporarily reset it to 0. Default: false.
    Method: set_use_custom_data(value: bool)
    Method: is_using_custom_data() → bool
*   **visible_instance_count** (int): Limits the number of instances drawn, -1 draws all instances. Changing this does not change the sizes of the buffers. Default: -1.
    Method: set_visible_instance_count(value: int)
    Method: get_visible_instance_count() → int
